FILE: ws.rs
MOD: api/ws
ROLE: WebSocket connection handler — upgrade, authenticate, stream pending messages, dispatch incoming stanzas
EP: handle_ws
STAB: volatile
INV:
  - WS authentication: X-Project, X-Project-Key, X-Agent-Name headers on upgrade — same identity model as HTTP
  - Qualified from="Name.Project" accepted at WS boundary (ARCH-04 fix): from= is validated by extracting name via resolve_agent_name
  - On connect: drain_pending messages delivered immediately before live streaming begins
  - Incoming stanzas dispatched via dispatch_stanza(validate_target=false) — target may not be registered yet
  - Error frames sent to client on: parse failure, from= mismatch, AmbiguousMention, CrossProjectDenied
  - On disconnect: broker.disconnect() called — session removed from in-memory map
  - WS path accepts cross-project channel posts (#channel.Project) — dispatch_stanza handles routing
LOOK: authentication block; error frame path; drain_pending on connect; handle_stanza from= check
CHK: cargo test; verify error frame test cases
CNTR: api/ws::handle_ws depends_on broker/state::authenticate
CNTR: api/ws::handle_ws depends_on broker/state::dispatch_stanza
DEPS-ON: broker/state; broker/delivery; stanza/types; stanza/parser
